                    <H1>Learning Difficulties in Mathematics in Framingham, Massachusetts</H1>
                    </TD>
                    </TR>
                    <TR>
                    <TD style="width: 100%;" align="left" valign="top">
                    <P><STRONG>Center for Teaching / Learning of Mathematics</STRONG> in Framingham, Massachusetts, has developed <a href="Tutoring-Services-Framingham-MA.html" target="_self">resources for teachers</a> to assist children and adults with their learning difficulties in mathematics. <BR>&nbsp; </P>
                    <H2>Teaching Resources </H2>
                    <P>We offer an extensive array of <a href="Mathematics-Teacher-Training-Videos-Framingham-MA.html" target="_self">mathematics publications</a> to help teachers and parents understand how children learn mathematics, why learning problems occur, and how to help them learn mathematics better. We conduct regular <a href="Mathematic-Teaching-Workshops-Framingham-MA.html" target="_self">workshops</a>, seminars, and lectures on topics that relate to child and adult student learning difficulties including dyscalculia. <BR>&nbsp; </P>
                    <H2>Diagnosis and Tutoring Services</H2>
                    <P><STRONG>Center for Teaching / Learning of Mathematics</STRONG> also provides learning difficulties diagnosis and tutoring services to help students of all ages overcome their difficulties. <a href="Teaching-Resources-Our-Founder-Framingham-MA.html" target="_self">Professor Sharma</a> works with individual students and with teachers and school administrators to design strategies to improve mathematics curriculum and instruction for all.</P>
                    <P style="TEXT-ALIGN: center"><a href="Learning-Difficulties-in-Mathematics-Contact-Framingham-MA.html" target="_self"><STRONG>Contact us</STRONG></a><STRONG> in Framingham, Massachusetts, for more information<BR>about how to overcome learning difficulties in mathematics.</STRONG></P>
                    </TD>
